---
import ProjectDetail from '../../layouts/ProjectDetail.astro';

const demoVideo = '/videos/aptrank-nyc-demo.mov';
---

<ProjectDetail
  title="AptRank NYC"
  description="Apartment ranking tool for NYC that scores units across your personal places, neighborhood safety, and proximity tradeoffs."
  tags={['Data', 'Python', 'Streamlit']}
  github="https://github.com/MariamKhubashvilii/Apartment-Search"
  accent="amber"
  demoVideo={demoVideo}
>
  <section class="project-grid">
    <article class="project-card summary-card">
      <h2>Project summary</h2>
      <p>
        AptRank helps you see apartments against your actual life — your office, your mum's place, your favourite café. Define the places that matter, weight each category, and get a ranked list with a clear explanation of every tradeoff.
      </p>
      <div class="summary-list">
        <div>
          <strong>Personal scoring</strong>
          <p>Weighted proximity to your frequent places using exponential decay — 1 km scores nearly full marks, 8 km scores much lower.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Safety layer</strong>
          <p>40+ NYC neighborhoods have baked-in safety scores that apply a multiplier to the final ranking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="project-card detail-card">
      <h2>What this project shows</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Weighted scoring across work, family, friends, and leisure.</li>
        <li>Exponential proximity decay instead of hard distance cutoffs.</li>
        <li>Diversity penalty for apartments far from high-priority places.</li>
        <li>Interactive map, stacked bar charts, and distance matrix.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="project-section">
    <div class="section-content">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        The final score combines personal rating (35%), weighted proximity (40%), neighborhood safety (15%), and a balance bonus (10%), then applies a safety multiplier. Bulk-add addresses, paste coordinates from Google Maps, or use autocomplete to build your candidate list.
      </p>

      <div class="section-grid">
        <div>
          <h3>Scoring factors</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Personal rating you assign per apartment</li>
            <li>Weighted proximity to frequent places</li>
            <li>Neighborhood safety multiplier</li>
            <li>Balance bonus for all-round performers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>Features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Address autocomplete and bulk geocoding</li>
            <li>Color-coded interactive map</li>
            <li>Radar chart comparing top 3 picks</li>
            <li>Full distance matrix in Analysis tab</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="project-section project-usage">
    <h2>Run it</h2>
    <p>
      Clone the repo, install dependencies, and run the Streamlit app. Add your frequent places with category weights, then drop in apartment candidates to see ranked scores with explanations.
    </p>
    <div class="usage-card">
      <div>
        <strong>Stack</strong>
        <p>Python 3.10+, Streamlit, Plotly, geocoding APIs</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Best for</strong>
        <p>NYC apartment hunters who care about proximity to real life, not just listing specs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProjectDetail>
